The error is caused by the normalization function which return-signature is `Object`. 

When called from java, there is no problem because the actual return type is `String`. But when called from H2 as an Alias Function, the `Object` return-signature is confusing H2 that then serializes the value into that &quot;aced000574001152323030&quot;-type string.

Explicitly changing the return-signature to `String` prevents that confusion and solves the issue:
```
public static String normalizeString(String source) {
    if (source==null) return null;
    String cleaned = source.replaceAll(&quot;[\\n\\r\\t]&quot;, &quot;&quot;);
    cleaned = Normalizer.normalize(cleaned, Normalizer.Form.NFD);
    cleaned = cleaned.replaceAll(&quot;[^\\p{ASCII}]&quot;, &quot;&quot;); // on vire tout ce qui n&#39;est pa ascii
    cleaned = cleaned.strip();
    return cleaned;
}

```

