    public Domain(V v) {
        if (v == null)
            System.out.println(&quot;Hello&quot;);
        else
            System.out.println(&quot;World&quot;);
    }
    public Domain() {} 
}
```
If Java were to run the second constructor instead, you wouldn&#39;t be able to use such logic.

